\begin{document}
\homework{16}{15 November }

Recall the primitive file IO commands as discussed in LYAHFGG.

\begin{program*}
\> writeFile :: FilePath -> String -> IO () \\
\> appendFile :: FilePath -> String -> IO () \\
\> readFile :: FilePath -> IO String \\
\end{program*}


\exercise{Write a function {\tt{cp fn1 fn2}} that copies file {\tt{fn1}} to file {\tt{fn2}}.
\begin{program*}
\> cpFile :: FilePath -> FilePath ->  IO()
\end{program*}
}

\exercise{Write a function {\tt{grep fn s}} that, given a filePath {\tt{fn}}, prints to the screen (think {\tt{putStr}}) all lines that contain the string {\tt{s}} as a substring.
\begin{program*}
\> grep :: FilePath ->  String -> IO()
\end{program*}
}



